<br>
Okay folks let's chat Hellblazer.  I'm gonna go back and reread all Mike's issues from the start.  Almost through Brian Azzarello's stuff.  I know alot of people slag on Az's run, but I find most of that is the long term fans (while newbies like myself tend to quite enjoy it).  I only jumped on board Hellblazer midway through his run (during the Guy Davis fill in issues), mostly because of the buzz the writer was getting and I heard that 100 bullets what tougher to get into.  I couldn't (and still can't really) compare Az's take on John as a character to other writers' takes, but I will say that his stories stand out as some of the most original, and eerie stories I've read in a long time.<br>
<br>
But now onto Mike's run...The most recent issue has been my favourite of the bunch.  Mike's ability to let us into John's head while at the same time keeping us at arms length is something that stands out for me in his run.  I'm learning more about John from the supporting cast than I am from John himself.  I'm not sure if Mike's conciously doing this, or if it's a nice side benefit of a well crafted story and characterization.  <br>
<br>
While Mike has given Lucifer depth...he's still best summarized as &quot;a total bastard&quot;.  But with John...while I think he goes out of his way to be called a bastard, there is so much more under the surface.  I've since read the first Ennis trade and the Ellis trade Haunted, and Ennis started to show us glimpses of the depth of John...and his device was having John face his own mortality.  Mike's technique of revealing through supporting cast (especially Jemma...I think that's her name) is something that's hitting all the right cords with me.<br>
<br>
I'm looking forward to checking out Mike's entire run again, not to mention the current arc.  <br>
<br>
Jason <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#111111><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/blucifer.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mcpeckham>mcpeckham</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#FFFF99>(11/14/03 10:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What Service!</span><hr size=1> We really need to kick up the action in here a bit.  I've been posting out to the newsgroups and bopping into the CBR and DC/Vertigo forums from time to time, but I don't want to turn into an evangelical gadfly...<br>
<br>
