<br>
You do have to admit the possibilites are tantalizing...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Here's what Mike's had to say about it in a past <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.comicbookresources.com/news/newsitem.cgi?id=1737" target="top">interview</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Interestingly, the response over at <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insanerantings.com/hell/" target="top">Straight to Hell</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (the major <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Hellblazer</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> board) was apparently fairly negative to the idea.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>One cast member you shouldn't expect to see is Lucifer Morningstar, the protagonist of &quot;Lucifer&quot; and whom many might expect, for commercial reasons, to have a crossover with John Constantine. While there are some similarities between the characters, admits Carey, it'd also be akin to a crossover between the current versions of Batman and the Black Panther: someone has to lose, meaning one character is undermined and that means fans won't be happy. &quot;I don't think we'll do a crossover,&quot; says Carey. &quot;John and Lucifer have a lot in common in some ways, and it's difficult to think of an encounter that wouldn't leave one of them looking belittled in some way. Cameos are something else, though. John popped up a long time ago, in 'Lucifer#5,' and I can see other subtle cross-fertilizations like this happening in future. But there are no compelling reasons for a crossover besides commercial ones. And by and large, readers don't seem to want it: I started a thread on the 'Hellblazer' message board asking that question, and mostly the responses were negative.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Papercut Fun</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#FFFF99>(12/22/03 8:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fluciferfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  How Long...</span><hr size=1> Has anyone heard how long Mike is planning to stay on Hellblazer?  I'm assuming he's still got alot of stories to tell, but I'm actually amazed at how fast time flies...he's put together quite a few arcs since he first signed on to guide Johnny C.'s stories.<br>
<br>
Jason<br>
